In commits 6f061c5cf3191aec15441d057e4bc852aedcd761 and
c5657cf3a05d245fca5cb88e027fd386a874176d, VTK did some refactoring to support
blurring on the skybox. Essentially, the skybox got pulled out of the normal
pipeline (PropArray) and into its own BackgroundProp receiving a unique camera
pass. However, that means it gets processed before any user's vtkLightPass is
executed. During the light pass, that's where
vtkOpenGlRenderer::LightingComplexity changes from the default -1 value to
a meaningful value.

The fact that the skybox has a -1 value for LightingComplexity triggers ubsan
warnings in that the -1 value is not a valid value for the enum.

The skybox doesn't actually *need* lighting, so it should turn off its own
lighting dependency by default.

--- Rendering/OpenGL2/vtkOpenGLSkybox.cxx
+++ Rendering/OpenGL2/vtkOpenGLSkybox.cxx
@@ -63,6 +63,7 @@ vtkOpenGLSkybox::vtkOpenGLSkybox()
   this->GetProperty()->SetDiffuse(0.0);
   this->GetProperty()->SetAmbient(1.0);
   this->GetProperty()->SetSpecular(0.0);
+  this->GetProperty()->SetLighting(false);
   this->OpenGLActor->SetProperty(this->GetProperty());
   this->CurrentRenderer = nullptr;
 }
